<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="244" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1428,1993]" pageId="9" pageNumber="244">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1824,1849]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="244" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species appears to be closely related to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Yang" baseAuthorityYear="1986" box="[816,945,1824,1848]" class="Insecta" family="Berothidae" genus="Berotha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="244" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bannana">
<emphasis box="[816,945,1824,1848]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="244">B. bannana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[1013,1098,1825,1848]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="9" pageNumber="244">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
in having similar gonocoxites 9 of hook-like apex, the complex of fused gonocoxites, gonapophyses and gonostyli 10 (= paramere-mediuncus complex) of a short bristles-bow, the fused gonocoxites 11 (= gonarcus) of arched sclerite and the hypandrium internum subtriangular, but it can be distinguished from the latter species by the male sternum 9 posteriorly concaved. In 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Yang" baseAuthorityYear="1986" box="[301,430,1968,1992]" class="Insecta" family="Berothidae" genus="Berotha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="244" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bannana">
<emphasis box="[301,430,1968,1992]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="244">B. bannana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the male sternum 9 is posteriorly truncate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
